        story: `<em>Tama opens his journal to a torn, scattered image — fragments of an old pottery shard.</em><br><br>"Friends! You're here — good, I wasn't sure the journal would actually find anyone.<br><br>My name's Tama. I'm training to be a wayfinder, like my grandmother Hina — best there's ever been in our village, everyone says so. Trouble is, her memory isn't what it used to be, and there are things she hasn't had the chance to teach me yet. Things I need to know before we sail.<br><br>This shard — see it? It came from my great-great-grandmother's village. Hina says if we piece it back together, it might show where our people truly began. I don't think I'm meant to figure this one out alone. Will you help me?"`,
