        story: `"A waka without a sail goes nowhere — but a sail without meaning is just cloth, Roa says. Real sails back home are woven, not painted — from pandanus leaves, in tight, repeating lines. She's been showing me how the pattern has to repeat perfectly, or the whole sail looks wrong. Today, make your square mean something the way a real woven sail does — not just decoration."`,
